 <label class="label">Fig. 3.</label>
 <caption class="caption">
  <p class="p">Testing annual 
   <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
    <math id="i60" class="math">
     <mi class="mi">P</mi>
    </math>
   </inline-formula> in the most recent decade for significant changes. The ordinate shows 
   <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
    <math id="i61" class="math">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</mi>
      <mi class="mi">P</mi>
     </mrow>
    </math>
   </inline-formula> (calculated as mean annual 
   <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
    <math id="i62" class="math">
     <mi class="mi">P</mi>
    </math>
   </inline-formula> for 2000–2009 less that for 1940–2009) as a function of the variance of the annual time series (1940–2009) for the GPCC observations. Each cross denotes one grid box. The curves (
   <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
    <math id="i63" class="math">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mn class="mn">1</mn>
      <msub class="msub">
       <mi class="mi">σ</mi>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</mi>
        <mi class="mi">P</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
    </math>
   </inline-formula>, 
   <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
    <math id="i64" class="math">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mn class="mn">2</mn>
      <msub class="msub">
       <mi class="mi">σ</mi>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</mi>
        <mi class="mi">P</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
    </math>
   </inline-formula>, 
   <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
    <math id="i65" class="math">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mn class="mn">3</mn>
      <msub class="msub">
       <mi class="mi">σ</mi>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</mi>
        <mi class="mi">P</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
    </math>
   </inline-formula>, and 
   <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
    <math id="i66" class="math">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mn class="mn">4</mn>
      <msub class="msub">
       <mi class="mi">σ</mi>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</mi>
        <mi class="mi">P</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
    </math>
   </inline-formula>) were estimated using 
   <xref ref-type="disp-formula" rid="eq1" class="xref">Eq. 
    <bold class="bold">1</bold>
   </xref>.
  </p>
